article.headline: San Francisco 89, Sacramento State 64
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Alan Wiggins 21 points led five starters in double digits as San Francisco erased a five-point halftime deficit to beat Sacramento State 89-64 on Tuesday night. Manny Quezada's 19 points, Antonio Kellog's 16 and Armondo Surrat's and Jay Watkins' 14 buckets each helped the Dons (2-0) shoot 78.6 percent from the floor in the second half. Wiggins also had 13 rebounds and three blocked shots. Alex Bausley had 21 points and 12 rebounds for the Hornets (1-2). Angle Alamo and Loren Leath added 10 points each for Sacramento State, who finished 5-for-19 from the free throw line. There were nine lead changes before the Hornets took command to lead 34-27 at the half, despite eight turnovers. Bausley lead the team with 12 points, eight rebounds, and two steals. The Dons then blazed out with a 23-0 run, topped off with a layup by Watkins to make the score 50-34 with 14:40 left. The Hornets didn't get their first bucket of the half until freshman Alonzo Young hit a free throw with 14:32 left to play. The Hornets managed to cut the Don's lead to 52-44, but San Francisco came back to stretch their advantage to 24 points after Surratt's layup made the score 83-59 with 2:46 to go. Sacramento State never got closer than 19 points the rest of the way.
